HEADWORD: Cassimere
<hw>Cas"si*mere</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>casimir</ets>, prob. of the same origin as E. <ets>cashmere</ets>.
Cf. <er>Kerseymere</er>.]</ety> <def>A thin, twilled, woolen cloth, used
for men's garments.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>kerseymere</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

